    "body": "<!--\r\n**PLEASE READ THIS FIRST:**\r\n- Do not use the bug and feature tracker for support requests. Use the `cython-users` mailing list instead.\r\n- Did you search for similar issues already? Please do, it helps to save us precious time that we otherwise could not invest into development.\r\n- Did you try the latest master branch or pre-release? It might already have what you want to report. Also see the [Changelog](https://github.com/cython/cython/blob/master/CHANGES.rst) regarding recent changes.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\nA caught exception referenced within a closure is not defined within the closure after the `except` block.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nCode to reproduce the behaviour:\r\n```cython\r\ntry:\r\n    raise ValueError(\"I'm an error\")\r\nexcept ValueError as err:\r\n    def print_err():\r\n        print(err)\r\nprint_err()\r\n# Traceback (most recent call last):\r\n#   File \"bar.py\", line 6, in <module>\r\n#     print_err()\r\n#   File \"bar.py\", line 5, in print_err\r\n#     print(err)\r\n# NameError: name 'err' is not defined\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nThe error should be defined within the closure.\r\n```cython\r\ntry:\r\n    raise ValueError(\"I'm an error\")\r\nexcept ValueError as err:\r\n    def print_err():\r\n        print(err)\r\nprint_err()\r\n# I'm an error\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Environment (please complete the following information):**\r\n - OS: macOS\r\n - Python version: 3.8.3\r\n - Cython version: 0.29.21\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nIf the closure is called before exiting the `except` block the error will be defined, but once called outside of the `except` block it will again be undefined.\r\n",
